The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                  BRIEFS

         
	Behrampore, Jan. 1: BSF jawans detained two schoolchildren all- egedly carrying heroin and trying to cross over to Bangladesh in Murshidabad last evening.
  
	The boys, one eight and the other nine, are in police custody. The police said they live in a village in Lalgola, about 250km from Calcutta. Around 300g of heroin was allegedly found on them.
    
	Calcutta: Jyoti Basu on Tuesday ruled out the Left parties forming a third front to fight the Congress and the BJP. We are going through a complex situation at the national level. The Left has to support the UPA government despite our differences, the CPM patriarch said.
    
	Chinsurah: House-wife Mehrunissa Bibi was allegedly strangled to death by her husband at Baghkhal in Hooghly, about 25km from Cal-cutta, following a tiff. Mohammad Nasim, a jute mill worker, is missing. 
    
	Rishra: Class XII student Amrita Saha committed suicide in Rishra, Hooghly, on Monday after allegedly being scolded by her parents for not paying attention to her studies. The 18-year-old girl hanged herself with her dupatta at her home, 30km from Calcutta.
                                                                               
